Class ConflictDetectingValueMerger<KEY extends NativeIndexKey<KEY>,​VALUE extends NativeIndexValue,​REPORT_TYPE>

    All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BlockBasedIndexPopulator.RecordingConflictDetector, ThrowingConflictDetector
    abstract class ConflictDetectingValueMerger<KEY extends NativeIndexKey<KEY>,​VALUE extends NativeIndexValue,​REPORT_TYPE>
extends Object
implements ValueMerger<KEY,​VALUE>
    ValueMerger which will merely detect conflict, not change any value if conflict, i.e. if the key already exists. After this merge has been used in a call to Writer.merge(Object, Object, ValueMerger) #checkConflict(REPORT_TYPE) can be called to check whether or not that call conflicted with an existing key. A call to #checkConflict(REPORT_TYPE) will also initialize the conflict flag.

      • merge

        public ValueMerger.MergeResult merge​(KEY existingKey,
                                     KEY newKey,
                                     VALUE existingValue,
                                     VALUE newValue)
        Description copied from interface: ValueMerger
        Merge an existing value with a new value.
        Specified by:
        merge in interface ValueMerger<KEY extends NativeIndexKey<KEY>,​VALUE extends NativeIndexValue>
        Parameters:
        existingKey - existing key
        newKey - new key
        existingValue - existing value
        newValue - new value
        Returns:
        result of the merge. What the various results mean:
        • ValueMerger.MergeResult.UNCHANGED the existing value will remain unchanged, i.e. no change to the tree whatsoever
        • ValueMerger.MergeResult.REPLACED the existing value will be overwritten with the contents of the new value
        • ValueMerger.MergeResult.MERGED the existing value will be overwritten with a value which is a merge between the existing and the new value, i.e. the contents of the existingValue parameter, as it looks after this call has completed will overwrite the value in the tree
        • ValueMerger.MergeResult.REMOVED the merged value resulted in something that should be removed from the tree. The existing key and value will be removed from the tree

      • controlConflictDetection

        void controlConflictDetection​(KEY key)
        To be called for a populated key that is about to be sent off to a Writer. GBPTree's ability to check for conflicts while applying updates is an opportunity, but also complicates some scenarios. This is why the strictness can be tweaked like this.
        Parameters:
        key - key to let know about conflict detection strictness.
